OL,6,FA sculpture based on characters from
OL,7,Fthe classic 1960s film Kes has been
OL,8,Funveiled opposite the author's former
OL,9,Fhome in .
OL,11,FBarry Hines wrote the novel A Kestrel
OL,12,Ffor a Knave, which was adapted for the
OL,13,Fscreen a year after its publication in
OL,14,F1967.
OL,16,FThe film Kes tells the story of
OL,17,Fnorthern schoolboy Billy Casper who
OL,18,Ffinds meaning in his life through his
OL,19,Fadopted kestrel. It won two Bafta
OL,20,Fawards and was nominated for a further
OL,21,Fthree.
